{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χᾰλῑνός</b> <br /> (<i>Aeolic dialect</i> χάλιννος probably in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Etymologicum Gudianum” 561.5)\">Refs</a>], ὁ, irregular <i>plural</i> χαλινά [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 4.1607, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Oppianus Anazarbensis Epicus “Halieutica - Poetae Bucolici et Didactici” 1.191, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.613c, 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.100, etc.\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]:—<b>bit,</b> once in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, ἐν δὲ χαλινοὺς γαμφηλῇς ἔβαλον 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.393; χαλινὸν ἐμβαλεῖν γνάθοις 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 492; χ. ἐξαιρεῖται 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitandi ratione” 3.2 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of the horse, χ. οὐκ ἐπίσταται φέρειν (<i>metaphorically</i> of Cassandra) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1066 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; χ. δέχεσθαι, λαμβάνειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitandi ratione” 3.2, 6.10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; λαβεῖν, ἔχειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1393b16, 21 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τὸν χ. ἐνδακεῖν champ the <b>bit,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 254d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the rider, δοτέον τὸν χ. one must give a horse the <b>rein,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitandi ratione” 10.12 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὀπίσω σπάσαι, ξυνέχειν ἀνάγκῃ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 254e, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “DDeor.” 25.1; [χ.] εἰς ἄκρον τὸ στόμα καθιέμενος 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitandi ratione” 6.9.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]—Expld. of the <b>bit,</b> opposed to reins (ἡνίαι), by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 1.148; so ἡνίας τε.. καὶ χ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 601c; χ. τινα χαλκεῖ ἐκδιδόντα σκευάσαι [prev. author] “Prm.” 127a; κατὰ [τὸν κυνόδοντα] ἐμβάλλεται ὁ χ. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 576b18, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 123 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1067 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but distinguished from στόμιον by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.215, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 207 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitandi ratione” 6.9, 10.9, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; and may be used generally for <b>bit and bridle,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.118, 4.64, “IG” 12.374.176, “PCair.Zen.” 659.11 (3rd c.BC). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, of <b>anything which curbs, restrains,</b> or <b>compels,</b> Ἀργοῦς χ., of an anchor, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.25 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χ. λινόδετοι, ={χαλινωτήρια}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 1043 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; παρθενίας χ. λύειν, of the virgin zone, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 8(7).48 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χαλινοῖς ἐν πετρίνοισιν, of Prometheus' bonds, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 562 (_anapaest meter_); Διὸς χ., of the will of Zeus, [prev. work] 672 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; χαλινῶν ἀναύδῳ μένει, of forcible constraint, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ag.” 238 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs</a>]; πολλῶν χαλινῶν ἔργον οἰάκων θ᾽ ἅμα, i.e. it requires much skill and force to guide, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 869 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τῷ δήμῳ χ. ἐμβαλεῖν ὕβρεως <b>a bridle to curb</b> their violence, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Comp. Per.Fab.” 1, compare 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Herm.” 82; τῆς γλώττης τὰ χ. 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.613c; ἐπέστω τῷ στόματι χ. 4th c.AD: Libanius Sophista “Epistulae” 315.4; χ. οὐδεὶς ὀμμάτων 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Vita Apollonii” 6.11. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> generally, <b>strap, thong,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 461 (dual). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> part of the <b>tackle of a ship,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscriptiones Graecae 22.1610.11,14. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>corner of the</b> horse's <b>mouth,</b> where the bit rests, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 2.90 (_plural_) \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; of the human mouth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Nicander Epicus “Alexipharmaca” 117, 223, “PUniv.Giss.” 44.7, (2nd-1st c.BC), 1st-2nd c.AD: Heliodorus Medicus cited in Orib 48.31.4, 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.100, “PSI” 9.1016.25 (2nd c.BC), 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “περὶ αἰτιῶν καὶ σημείων ὀξέων παθῶν” 1.9, 5th c.AD: Caelius Aurelianus Medicus “TP” 1.4, 6th c.AD: Aëtius Medicus 8.27 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; but, ={ἡ σύνδεσις τῶν γνάθων}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Rufus Medicus “περὶ ὀνομασίας” 53, compare 6th c.AD: Aëtius Medicus 8.40. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__IV.2</b></Level3> <b>fangs of serpents,</b> from their shape and position in the mouth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Nicander Epicus “Theriaca” 234. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5469","accentedUnicode":"χαλινός","shortDef":"bit, bridle","mediumDef":"bit, bridle <br /><b>a bridle, bit,</b> <ref='Jas.3.3'>Jas. 3:3;</ref> <ref='Rev.14.20'>Rev. 14:20</ref>*","stepGloss":"bridle","stepTransliteration":"chalinos","count":2,"_es_Definition":"freno, brida (de caballo)","_zh_tw_Definition":"馬勒, 嚼環","_zh_Definition":"马勒, 嚼环","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"hàm thiết ngựa; dây cương (ngựa)","_zh_tw_Gloss":"嚼環","_es_Gloss":"freno","_zh_Gloss":"嚼环"}]}